b9hAd5U4Jrk.title: Pokemon Center exclusive Chilling Reign Elite Trainer Box : Error Box!
b9hAd5U4Jrk.description:
The Pokemon Center had exclusive Chilling Reign Elite Trainer boxes, that I immediately had to jump on, but then later I found out that they messed up and didn't include all 10 included packs, so now let's open them up to really get a look at what came inside! Unlike the standard elite trainer box, the pokemon center exclusive chilling reign elite trainer box was advertised as 10 packs, a metallic coin, and metal dice, which isn't much, but at $10 more, it's not too bad now that we're on this end of the 2020 hype. Regardless I was quite excited to find out about the pokemon center chilling reign elite trainer box, and the fact that this might be a recurring product for different sets.

Also for those who were speculating that this is where potentially a special delivery charizard was going to be included, well you can clearly see for yourself based on the contents shown here. I will say though, that compared to other sets, it did feel like chilling reign was pretty available via the pokemon center website in comparison to something like shinning fates, so regardless, I was quite happy to have this opportunity without having an enormous struggle!

lAbfAp3h3-4.description:

There's no big difference between the blue and the red box, but it just uses slightly different designs and the color.

I'm trying to continue adding to my Battle Styles binder, and lucky for me Battle Styles is one of the most affordable products out there at the moment, from the booster box to the ETB, and seeing as I needed a nice place to store my Battle Styles bulk cards, I had no problem picking up this box!

If you're out there looking to just being able to open an elite trainer box, this really could be the product for you, this isn't a favorite set for everyone, but in all honesty, it's not bad, and as far as the higher end cards of the set like the alternate art Tyranitar V, or even just the VMAX cards like Victini VMAX or Flapple VMAX, in my opinion you can't go wrong here for the price!

dNKhpn9KNxI.title: Pokemon Center Eevee Heroes Espeon Box Opening! The Eeveelution Set
dNKhpn9KNxI.description:
I'm so excited to be able to open this out of this world box. If you don't know what this is, this is the Pokemon Center Eevee Heroes Espeon Box, and thanks for checking out this opening! This box is also known as the Eeveelution set. This is such a cool set in general where the main theme is Eevee and it's evolutions, and therefore has some strong cards. One of the key components to this whole set is definitely the Espeon VMAX promo card which is just stunning, but then again so are all of the Eevee Heroes alternative art work. This box was definitely on the pricey side of things, but should you decided to buy one for yourself, this will give you an idea on what the Eevee Heroes VMAX Special set contents might be like for yourself. I have never opened a Pokemon Center gym set box, so I was really happy to make this the first for your education and entertainment.

dTcBbNgOe1o.title: Opening first elite trainer box
dTcBbNgOe1o.description:
This is a video of me opening first elite trainer box. I had never opened one up to this point, so this was quite a cool one to start with. For those who have been on the fence about ETB's or specifically if some have wondered to themselves: Should you buy shining fates products, I feel like this was a good sample of a video to look from. I've tried other Shining Fates products, such as the Cramorant tin, and the Pikachu V Collection, but it was nice to have 10 consecutive booster packs. I've seen many other ETB openings, but I gotta say that the shining fates elite trainer box opening is something else! One of the things that's great about this is the fact that it comes with an Eevee vmax promo guaranteed, opposed to some of the other ETB's that have no promo card inside. If you've never picked up a pokemon elite trainer box, I can highly recommend the Shining Fates one!

If you've opened one yourself, what kind of pulls did you have? Did you pull a Ditto VMax Shiny? Perhaps some amazing rare pokemon? Maybe some baby shinies like Dragapult baby shiny? Let me know!

0CkK09ZI5IM.title: Pokemon Collection Battle : Opening Pokemon Meowth VMax and Pikachu V
0CkK09ZI5IM.description:
Pokemon Collection Battle : Opening Pokemon Meowth VMax and Pikachu V collection boxes

This is the great battle of natural foes Meowth vs Pikachu!

Today I've decided to put Pikachu up against Meowth in a collection box battle! Meowth of course has the Meowth VMAX Collection box, and with the shinning fates set came out a Pikachu V Collection box set.

In general Shining fates is known for pulling hits after hits with it's amazing rares, and the entirety of the shiny vault collection, one might say that this is a done battle, but looking at the Meowth collection set, it has a great variety of packs, we've got an XY Evolutions, Unified Minds, and not 1, but 2 Cosmic Eclipse! Aside from the packs in general, we have special V cards for both, but long boi Meowth has a VMAX card. If that wasn't enough to call these great sets to begin with they also come with awesome Jumbo cards!

Assuming you'd see both of these on a shelf, which one would you be inclined to pick up?

y3jp84ylFaQ.title: I bought my first graded card : my first graded pokemon card
y3jp84ylFaQ.description:
I bought my first graded card : my first graded pokemon card

I've been buying things off of ebay lately, and I've also managed to accumulate a few loose Pokemon booster packs, so I've decided to show all of it, to you all! This is a video of many openings, I will be opening mystery pokemon items and showing my first graded card! We've got the Pokemon mystery power cube opening, a card re-pack that can only be described as an ebay Pokemon mystery pack opening, I also decide on opening Pokemon McDonalds cards, and I finally get to opening Pokemon booster packs for Youtube!

As far as opening Pokemon card packs, I'm going to be opening rebel clash pack, opening sword and shield booster pack and opening champions path booster packs.

Finally I get to show off my ebay psa pokemon card that I've acquired recently, which makes it possible for me to say that I bought my first graded card! I do plan on getting cards graded, but as a start, I'm really glad to have my first graded pokemon card.

TQRgAzBIp08.title: Twitch streamer Pokemon card collection
TQRgAzBIp08.description:
Twitch streamer Pokemon card collection

Like many, I collected pokemon cards when all of this started, and again like many I stopped after some time, only to have this ignited all over again. I decided to show off some gems ranging from simple promo holos to some cards that made a deeper impression on me. By no means is this everything, but just what I currently put into top loaders that I'm considering maybe taking to get grading because they bring me lots of joy.

As a note, this footage was taken from my twitch stream, and condensed for youtube viewing pleasures. I do plan on posting more pokemon content on here that may or may not be from my twitch streams. If you prefer, feel free to check me out at twitch.tv/kirksicle as this was part of my twitch stream pokemon collection, but in general I'm a fan of showing pokemon cards on stream, but for now it's been pokemon cards twitch stream.

As far as what's in the collection itself it's a bit sporadic and there's a bit of everything from a pokemon legendary collection set card, to pokemon gym heroes 1st edition cards, pokemon base set 1st edition, 1st edition Charizard, feel free to rate my pokemon cards!

From the collection I've shown, which ones did you like? Also, what cards were you able to save from all these years? Any honorable vintage mentions?

5PWshbtPkvg.title: Get gud at Crash 2 : Crash Bandicoot 2 twitch stream - Gold Relics 2
5PWshbtPkvg.description:
Get gud at Crash 2 : Crash Bandicoot 2 twitch Stream - Gold relics compilation 2

For those who have failed many times and need some encouragement for improving in Crash 2, this is my second short compilation of myself streaming Crash 2 and making gold relic attempts so I could eventually get the platinum trophy on PlayStation.

This was all captured as part of my crash 2 stream and by no means did this happen quickly, I started off initially as terrible, but then ended up not doing terrible at Crash 2. Originally I was trying to get the platinum trophy but I wasn't counting on time relics as being a thing that needed to be done, which then created the need to play all these levels so many times. I never thought I'd be getting good at Crash Bandicoot 2, but through this journey I could at least see a glimpse of that.

Make sure to Like and subscribe, If you liked these Crash 2 streams, or if you're a fan of more Crash 2 twitch streams!

Also to catch the streams live, go check it out at:
https://www.twitch.tv/Kirksicle
